Add a \`watch <directory>\` CLI command that monitors .mbtv files and recompiles on change.

The incremental compilation infrastructure (\`IncrementalCompiler\` using mizchi/ripple) is already in place — cached compile returns in ~0.3µs for unchanged files. A file watcher would complete the development loop.

## Needed

- Directory scanning for .mbtv files
- Polling-based change detection (no native fsevents in MoonBit)
- Output compiled files (.client.mbt, .server.mbt, .css)
- Console output showing what changed